// Service-specific FAQs for ServiceSchema
const walkoutFAQs = [
  {
    question: "How much does a foundation walkout door cost in Toronto?",
    answer: "Foundation walkout costs depend on complexity: Basic egress door cut $8,650-12,000, window to door conversion $6,500-10,000, full walkout with stairs $27,000-40,000, and premium walkout with patio $43,000+. Factors include wall thickness, excavation depth, structural requirements, moisture protection complexity, and finishing options. All prices include permits and engineering."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does foundation walkout installation take?",
    answer: "Timeline varies by project scope: Simple door cut-out 3-5 days, window to door conversion 2-3 days, full walkout with stairs 2-3 weeks, premium walkout with patio 3-4 weeks. Includes excavation, cutting, installation, waterproofing, and basic finishing. Weather and soil conditions can affect timeline."
  },
  {
    question: "What are the benefits of a foundation walkout door?",
    answer: "Foundation walkouts provide NBC code compliance, fire safety egress, separate entrance for legal suites, $2,200+/month rental income potential, 5-10% property value increase, natural light and ventilation, improved lower level functionality, and enhanced home marketability. Professional installation ensures structural integrity and moisture protection."
  },
  {
    question: "When do I need a foundation walkout or door?",
    answer: "Foundation doors are required for: legal lower level apartments, NBC fire safety compliance, lower levels with heating equipment, emergency egress from bedrooms, areas >25m long, separate home office access, and rental suite creation. Required by building code for safety and increasingly demanded by buyers."
  }
