    name: "Full Walkout with Stairs",
    price: "$27,000-40,000",
    description: "Complete walkout entrance with double door or patio opening, full excavation and grading, engineered support system, premium doors and hardware, complete waterproofing, concrete stairs with railings, drainage system, and 5-year warranty."
  },
  {
    name: "Premium Suite Entrance",
    price: "$43,000+",
    description: "Luxury walkout with sliding glass doors, covered entrance/awning, interlocking stone patio, retaining walls if needed, lighting system, premium landscaping, and 10-year warranty. Custom designed for maximum value."
  }
];

const faqItems = [
  {
    question: "Why do I need a foundation walkout or door?",
    answer: "NBC requires below-grade access for fire safety and rescue operations. Every lower level needs a door, window, or opening to facilitate occupant escape and firefighter access. This is especially critical for areas with heating equipment or storage. Legal lower level apartments require a separate entrance. Walkouts also add significant value, provide natural light, and improve area livability."
  },
  {
    question: "What are the NBC requirements for basement access?",
    answer: "For single dwelling units: At least one door or window opening is required from each lower level. For multiple units or areas >25m long: Direct outdoor access required with minimum 1100mm (43\") height and 550mm (22\") width, located maximum 900mm (35\") above floor. Standard doors must be 36\" wide minimum. Emergency exits require 3.8 sq ft opening area. All openings must be operable from inside without tools or keys."
  },
  {
    question: "Can any foundation wall be cut for a door?",
    answer: "Not all walls are suitable for cutting. Load-bearing walls require extensive reinforcement. Block walls are easier to cut than poured concrete. The location must avoid utility lines, maintain proper distances from corners (minimum 4 feet), and ensure adequate header support. Our structural engineer assesses each situation and designs appropriate reinforcement to maintain structural integrity."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does a walkout installation take?",
    answer: "Timeline depends on scope: Simple door cut-out: 3-5 days. Window to door conversion: 2-3 days. Full walkout with stairs: 2-3 weeks. Luxury walkout with patio: 3-4 weeks. This includes excavation, cutting, installation, waterproofing, and basic finishing. Weather and soil conditions can affect timeline. We provide detailed schedules and minimize disruption to your home."
  },
  {
    question: "Will cutting my foundation wall cause structural problems?",
    answer: "When properly engineered, foundation cutting is completely safe. We install steel or concrete lintels to carry loads around the opening, use temporary supports during cutting, and reinforce surrounding areas as needed. Our P.Eng certified designs ensure structural integrity. We've completed 500+ foundation cuts without any structural issues. All work includes structural warranty."
  },
  {
    question: "What about waterproofing around the new door?",
    answer: "Moisture protection is critical for walkouts. We install rubberized membrane around entire opening, proper water removal below door threshold, weeping tile connection to drainage system, and slope grading away from entrance. Window wells include gravel drainage base. All installations include interior and exterior protection with 10-year warranty against water infiltration."
  },
  {
    question: "Do I need a permit for a basement door?",
    answer: "Yes, permits are required for any foundation modification. This includes building permit for structural work, electrical permit if adding lighting, and plumbing permit if affecting water removal. Some municipalities also require engineering drawings and site plan amendments. We handle all permit applications and coordinate inspections. Unpermitted work can result in fines and problems when selling."
  },
  {
    question: "How much value does a walkout add to my home?",
    answer: "Walkouts typically add 5-10% to property value ($54,000-100,000 in Toronto). Benefits include: enables legal lower level apartment ($2,200+/month rental income), increases natural light and ventilation, provides separate entrance for privacy, improves emergency egress safety, and makes area feel like above-grade space. ROI is typically 150-200% of installation cost."
  }
];
---

<Layout title="Basement Walkout & Door Cutting Services Toronto | Foundation Opening Experts">
  <ServiceSchema 
    serviceName="Lower Level Walkout & Door Cutting Services"
    description="Professional foundation opening services for lower level walkouts, emergency exits, and separate entrances. P.Eng certified structural design, moisture control, and NBC code compliance for Toronto homes."
    priceRange="$6,500-40,000+"
    areaServed={['Toronto', 'Mississauga', 'Brampton', 'Vaughan', 'Markham', 'Richmond Hill', 'North York', 'Scarborough']}
    offers={walkoutOffers}
    faqs={walkoutFAQs}
  />
  <Hero
    title="Lower Level Walkout & Door Cutting"
    subtitle="Professional Foundation Opening Services. Create Separate Entrances, Emergency Exits, and Walkout Access."
    backgroundImage="/images/walkout-hero.webp"
    ctaText="Get Free Quote"
    ctaLink="/contact"
  />

